The paper deals with discounted-sum games, which are a common model in game theory (cs.GT) and reinforcement learning (cs.AI). The main focus of the paper is on regret minimization, which is a key concept in both of these fields. The paper also introduces a new class of strategies, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper includes results on the computational complexity of regret minimization, which could be relevant to researchers in algorithms and complexity theory (cs.DS).
